This is with it, right? Or is it only if they were told/exposed to the story originally from one of the tribe? I.e., would the exposed researcher be able to infect someone else with his story? Because if that's the case, this is clearly a Keter due to the INCREDIBLE difficulty in containing it. If the infectious story has to originate from a member of Tribe A, then it's somewhat easier to contain, and I agree that Euclid would be more appropriate.

